#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Puññābhisandavagga "
msgstr "4. Overflowing Merit "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn55.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Dutiyadevapadasutta "
msgstr "35. Footprints of the Gods (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.35:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, devānaṃ devapadāni avisuddhānaṃ sattānaṃ visuddhiyā apariyodātānaṃ sattānaṃ pariyodapanāya. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four footprints of the gods are in order to purify unpurified beings and cleanse unclean beings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn55.35:2.1"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "Firstly, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha: "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.3"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti. "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.4"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.5"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho devānaṃ devapadan’ti? "
msgstr "‘What now is the footprint of the gods?’ "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.6"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

# NOTE: Interesting use of eterahi; is this a coded message about the reformed impulses of the Gods?
msgctxt "sn55.35:2.7"
msgid "‘abyābajjhaparame khvāhaṃ etarahi deve suṇāmi. "
msgstr "‘I hear that these days the gods consider non-harming to be supreme. "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.8"
msgid "Na ca kho panāhaṃ kiñci byābādhemi tasaṃ vā thāvaraṃ vā. "
msgstr "But I don’t hurt any creature firm or frail. "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.9"
msgid "Addhāhaṃ devapadadhammasamannāgato viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I definitely live in possession of a footprint of the gods.’ "

msgctxt "sn55.35:2.10"
msgid "Idaṃ paṭhamaṃ devānaṃ devapadaṃ avisuddhānaṃ sattānaṃ visuddhiyā apariyodātānaṃ sattānaṃ pariyodapanāya. "
msgstr "This is the first footprint of the gods in order to purify unpurified beings and cleanse unclean beings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn55.35:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.35:3.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …. "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.394, sc4
msgctxt "sn55.35:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a noble disciple’s ethical conduct is loved by the noble ones, unbroken, impeccable, spotless, and unmarred, liberating, praised by sensible people, not mistaken, and leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.2"
msgid "So iti paṭisañcikkhati: "
msgstr "Then they reflect: "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.3"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho devānaṃ devapadan’ti? "
msgstr "‘What now is the footprint of the gods?’ "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.4"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti: "
msgstr "They understand: "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.5"
msgid "‘abyābajjhaparame khvāhaṃ etarahi deve suṇāmi. "
msgstr "‘I hear that these days the gods consider non-harming to be supreme. "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.6"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ kiñci byābādhemi tasaṃ vā thāvaraṃ vā. "
msgstr "But I don’t hurt any creature firm or frail. "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.7"
msgid "Addhāhaṃ devapadadhammasamannāgato viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I definitely live in possession of a footprint of the gods.’ "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.8"
msgid "Idaṃ catutthaṃ devānaṃ devapadaṃ avisuddhānaṃ sattānaṃ visuddhiyā apariyodātānaṃ sattānaṃ pariyodapanāya. "
msgstr "This is the fourth footprint of the gods in order to purify unpurified beings and cleanse unclean beings. "

msgctxt "sn55.35:4.9"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri devānaṃ devapadāni avisuddhānaṃ sattānaṃ visuddhiyā apariyodātānaṃ sattānaṃ pariyodapanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "These four footprints of the gods are in order to purify unpurified beings and cleanse unclean beings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.35:4.10"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

